re CLI.\\n     4→\\n     5→## Structure\\n     6→\\n     7→This skill is split between an orchestrator skill and a plugin with individual commands:\\n     8→\\n     9→### Orchestrator (skill)\\n    10→\\n    11→- `.claude/skills/agent-integration/SKILL.md` — Runs all 3 phases sequentially as `/agent-integration`\\n    12→\\n    13→### Individual Commands (plugin)\\n    14→\\n    15→- `.claude/plugins/agent-integration/commands/research.md` — `/agent-integration:research`\\n    16→- `.claude/plugins/agent-integration/commands/write-tests.md` — `/agent-integration:write-tests`\\n    17→- `.claude/plugins/agent-integration/commands/implement.md` — `/agent-integration:implement`\\n    18→\\n    19→## Loading the Plugin\\n    20→\\n    21→The individual `:` subcommands require the plugin to be loaded. Options:\\n    22→\\n    23→```bash\\n    24→# Option 1: Load via --plugin-dir flag\\n    25→claude --plugin-dir .claude/plugins/agent-integration/\\n    26→\\n    27→# Option 2: Shell alias (add to ~/.zshrc)\\n    28→alias claude-dev='claude --plugin-dir .claude/plugins/agent-integration/'\\n    29→```\\n    30→\\n    31→## Commands\\n    32→\\n    33→| Command | Purpose | Output |\\n    34→|---------|---------|--------|\\n    35→| `/agent-integration` | Run all 3 phases | Full integration |\\n    36→| `/agent-integration:research` | Assess compatibility | Compatibility report + test script |\\n    37→| `/agent-integration:write-tests` | Write E2E test suite | AgentRunner + test scenarios |\\n    38→| `/agent-integration:implement` | Build agent via TDD | Go package under `cmd/entire/cli/agent/` |\\n    39→\\n    40→## Typical Workflow\\n    41→\\n    42→```\\n    43→# Full pipeline (single session)\\n    44→/agent-integration\\n    45→\\n    46→# Or individual phases\\n    47→/agent-integration:research       # 1. Can this agent integrate?\\n    48→/agent-integration:write-tests    # 2. What should the tests look like?\\n    49→/agent-integration:implement      # 3. Build it with TDD\\n    50→```\\n    51→\\n    52→## Parameters\\n    53→\\n    54→Collected once and reused across commands:\\n    55→\\n    56→| Parameter | Example | Description |\\n    57→|-----------|---------|-------------|\\n    58→| `AGENT_NAME` | \\\"Windsurf\\\" | Human-readable name |\\n    59→| `AGENT_SLUG` | \\\"windsurf\\\" | Lowercase slug |\\n    60→| `AGENT_BIN` | \\\"windsurf\\\" | CLI binary name |\\n    61→| `LIVE_COMMAND` | \\\"windsurf --project .\\\" | Launch command |\\n    62→| `EVENTS_OR_UNKNOWN` | \\\"unknown\\\" | Known hook events or \\\"unknown\\\" |\\n    63→\\n    64→## Architecture References\\n    65→\\n    66→- Agent interface: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go`\\n    67→- Event types: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/event.go`\\n    68→- Implementation guide: `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md`\\n    69→- Integration checklist: `docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md`\\n    70→- E2E test infrastructure: `e2e/`\\n    71→- Existing agents: Discover via `Glob(\\\"cmd/entire/cli/agent/*/\\\")`\\n    72→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"43215d2c-181f-4236-8d5e-1da631ab6805\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:45:26.370Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a4f91b1ff72fb48e5\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01VEiM5bmK9sCnTqaXtpfURh\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01CHSGpd9mgfnLtAUuoyLCRa\",\"uuid\":\"37ce2c3d-102e-4c09-a7a6-3c3dafb26a60\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:45:26.370Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"37ce2c3d-102e-4c09-a7a6-3c3dafb26a60\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"00468b34-359e-43a2-b0bb-30677f1aee5e\",\"version\":\"2.1.71\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage-local-only\",\"slug\":\"delegated-hatching-sundae\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:45:27.941Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_013hQRuTRH7xogjTQh3hndeQ\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01DH9NdY9QyGzUgUpDCTKvuY\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/.claude/skills/agent-integration/researcher.md\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1085,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":53473,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":1085,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":2,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYno6eS1xpriZS7V1B8y7\",\"uuid\":\"8a3bdabe-5145-4667-947b-9e39e71ca85b\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a4f91b1ff72fb48e5\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01VEiM5bmK9sCnTqaXtpfURh\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01CHSGpd9mgfnLtAUuoyLCRa\",\"uuid\":\"b7f9265d-206f-424a-bc03-33ba970e38e6\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:45:27.941Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"b7f9265d-206f-424a-bc03-33ba970e38e6\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"00468b34-359e-43a2-b0bb-30677f1aee5e\",\"version\":\"2.1.71\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage-local-only\",\"slug\":\"delegated-hatching-sundae\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01DH9NdY9QyGzUgUpDCTKvuY\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Research Command\\n     2→\\n     3→Assess whether a target AI coding agent's hook/lifecycle model is compatible with the Entire CLI before writing any Go code.\\n     4→\\n     5→## Procedure\\n     6→\\n     7→### Phase 1: Understand Entire's Expectations\\n     8→\\n     9→Read `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` to understand what Entire expects from agents: EventType names, required interfaces, hook patterns, and lifecycle flow. This gives you the vocabulary to map the target agent's native hooks to Entire's event model.\\n    10→\\n    11→You may also reference `cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go` and `cmd/entire/cli/agent/event.go` for exact interface signatures and EventType constants. Prefer `agent-guide.md` as the primary source, but the source files are the ground truth if the guide is out of date. Avoid reading other internal files (`hook_registry.go`, `lifecycle.go`, strategy code) — the implementer handles those, and architecture tests enforce this boundary at the code level.\\n    12→\\n    13→### Phase 2: Static Capability Checks\\n    14→\\n    15→Non-destructive CLI probing. Record PASS/WARN/FAIL for each:\\n    16→\\n    17→| Check | Command | PASS | FAIL |\\n    18→|-------|---------|------|------|\\n    19→| Binary present | `command -v $AGENT_BIN` | Found | Not found (blocker) |\\n    20→| Help output | `$AGENT_BIN --help` or `$AGENT_BIN help` | Available | No help |\\n    21→| Version info | `$AGENT_BIN --version` or `$AGENT_BIN version` | Available | N/A |\\n    22→| Hook keywords | Scan help for: hook, lifecycle, callback, event, trigger, pre-, post-, plugin, extension | Found | None found |\\n    23→| Session keywords | Scan help for: session, resume, continue, history, transcript, context | Found | None found |\\n    24→| Config directory | Check `~/.$AGENT_SLUG/`, `~/.config/$AGENT_SLUG/`, `./$AGENT_SLUG/`, `./.${AGENT_SLUG}/` | Found | None found |\\n    25→| Documentation | Web search for hook/plugin/extension docs | Found | None found |\\n    26→\\n    27→### Phase 3: Test Script Creation\\n    28→\\n    29→Based on Phase 2 findings, create an **agent-specific** test script:\\n    30→\\n    31→```\\n    32→scripts/test-$AGENT_SLUG-agent-integration.sh\\n    33→```\\n    34→\\n    35→The script is tailored to the specific agent's hook mechanism (not a generic template). Adapt the hook wiring section based on what Phase 2 discovered.\\n    36→\\n    37→**Script structure:**\\n    38→\\n    39→```bash\\n    40→#!/usr/bin/env bash\\n    41→set -euo pipefail\\n    42→\\n    43→AGENT_NAME=\\\"...\\\"\\n    44→AGENT_SLUG=\\\"...\\\"\\n    45→AGENT_BIN=\\\"...\\\"\\n    46→PROBE_DIR=\\\".entire/tmp/probe-${AGENT_SLUG}-$(date +%s)\\\"\\n    47→```\\n    48→\\n    49→**Required sections:**\\n    50→\\n    51→1. **Static checks** — Re-runnable binary/version/help checks\\n    52→2. **Hook wiring** — Create workspace-local config that intercepts hooks and dumps stdin JSON to `$PROBE_DIR/captures/<event-name>-<timestamp>.json`\\n    53→3. **Run modes:**\\n    54→   - `--run-cmd '<cmd>'` — Automated: launch agent, wait, collect\\n    55→   - `--manual-live` — Interactive: user runs agent manually, presses Enter\\n    56→4. **Capture collection** — List and pretty-print all payload files\\n    57→5. **Cleanup** — Restore original config (unless `--keep-config`)\\n    58→6. **Verdict** — PASS/WARN/FAIL per lifecycle event + COMPATIBLE/PARTIAL/INCOMPATIBLE\\n    59→\\n    60→### Phase 4: Execution & Analysis\\n    61→\\n    62→Run the script and analyze:\\n    63→\\n    64→1. **Execute**: `chmod +x scripts/test-$AGENT_SLUG-agent-integration.sh && scripts/test-$AGENT_SLUG-agent-integration.sh --manual-live`\\n    65→2. **For each captured payload**: show command, artifact path, decoded JSON\\n    66→3. **Lifecycle mapping**: native hook name → Entire EventType\\n    67→\\n    68→### Phase 5: Implementation One-Pager\\n    69→\\n    70→Write the research findings to `cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_PACKAGE/AGENT.md` as a structured one-pager that the test-writer and implementer phases will use as their single source of agent-specific information.\\n    71→\\n    72→**Create the agent package directory first** (if it doesn't exist):\\n    73→\\n    74→```bash\\n    75→mkdir -p cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_PACKAGE\\n    76→```\\n    77→\\n    78→**Write the one-pager using this template:**\\n    79→\\n    80→```markdown\\n    81→# $AGENT_NAME — Integration One-Pager\\n    82→\\n    83→## Verdict: COMPATIBLE / PARTIAL / INCOMPATIBLE\\n    84→\\n    85→## Static Checks\\n    86→| Check | Result | Notes |\\n    87→|-------|--------|-------|\\n    88→| Binary present | PASS/FAIL | path |\\n    89→| Help available | PASS/FAIL | |\\n    90→| Version info | PASS/FAIL | version string |\\n    91→| Hook keywords | PASS/FAIL | keywords found |\\n    92→| Session keywords | PASS/FAIL | keywords found |\\n    93→| Config directory | PASS/FAIL | path |\\n    94→| Documentation | PASS/FAIL | URL |\\n    95→\\n    96→## Binary\\n    97→- Name: `$AGENT_BIN`\\n    98→- Version: ...\\n    99→- Install: ... (how to install if not present)\\n   100→\\n   101→## Hook Mechanism\\n   102→- Config file: `~/.config/$AGENT_SLUG/settings.json` (exact path)\\n   103→- Config format: JSON / YAML / TOML\\n   104→- Hook registration: ... (how hooks are declared — JSON objects, env vars, etc.)\\n   105→- Hook names and when they fire:\\n   106→  | Native Hook Name | When It Fires | Entire EventType |\\n   107→  |-----------------|---------------|-----------------|\\n   108→  | `on_session_start` | Agent session begins | `SessionStart` |\\n   109→  | ... | ... | ... |\\n   110→- Valid Entire EventTypes: `SessionStart`, `TurnStart`, `TurnEnd`, `Compaction`, `SessionEnd`, `SubagentStart`, `SubagentEnd`\\n   111→- Hook input (stdin JSON): ... (exact fields with example payload)\\n   112→\\n   113→## Transcript\\n   114→- Location: `~/.config/$AGENT_SLUG/sessions/<id>/transcript.jsonl`\\n   115→- Format: JSONL / JSON array / other\\n   116→- Session ID extraction: ... (from hook payload field or directory name)\\n   117→- Example entry: `{\\\"role\\\": \\\"user\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"...\\\"}`\\n   118→\\n   119→## Config Preservation\\n   120→- Keys to preserve when modifying: ... (or \\\"use read-modify-write on entire file\\\")\\n   121→- Settings that affect hook behavior: ...\\n   122→\\n   123→## CLI Flags\\n   124→- Non-interactive prompt: `$AGENT_BIN --prompt \\\"...\\\" --no-confirm`\\n   125→- Interactive mode: `$AGENT_BIN` (or \\\"not supported\\\")\\n   126→- Relevant env vars: ...\\n   127→\\n   128→## Gaps & Limitations\\n   129→- ... (anything that doesn't map cleanly)\\n   130→\\n   131→## Captured Payloads\\n   132→- See `.entire/tmp/probe-$AGENT_SLUG-*/captures/` for raw JSON captures\\n   133→```\\n   134→\\n   135→**Key points about the one-pager:**\\n   136→\\n   137→- The **Entire EventType mapping** (which native hook → which EventType) uses the event names learned from `agent-guide.md` in Phase 1. The researcher can do this mapping because it's a simple table — it doesn't need Entire source code.\\n   138→- Fill in every section with concrete values from Phases 2-4. Don't leave placeholders.\\n   139→- If a section doesn't apply (e.g., no transcript support), say so explicitly.\\n   140→- This file persists as development documentation — future maintainers will reference it.\\n   141→\\n   142→### Phase 6: Commit\\n   143→\\n   144→Use `/commit` to commit all files.\\n   145→\\n   146→## Blocker Handling\\n   147→\\n   148→If blocked at any point (auth, sandbox, binary not found):\\n   149→\\n   150→1. State the exact blocker\\n   151→2. Provide the exact command for the user to run manually\\n   152→3. Explain what output to paste back\\n   153→4. Continue with provided output\\n   154→\\n   155→## Constraints\\n   156→\\n   157→- **No Go code.** This command produces a one-pager and test script only.\\n   158→- **Non-destructive.** All artifacts go under `.entire/tmp/` (gitignored). The one-pager goes in the agent package directory.\\n   159→- **Agent-specific scripts.** Adapt based on Phase 2 findings, not a generic template.\\n   160→- **Ask, don't assume.** If the hook mechanism is unclear, ask the user.\\n   161→- **External focus.** Prefer `agent-guide.md` for Entire's expectations. You may reference `agent.go` and `event.go` for exact names, but avoid deeper internals — architecture tests enforce the boundary at the code level.\\n   162→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"2488d9b0-