wd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"00468b34-359e-43a2-b0bb-30677f1aee5e\",\"version\":\"2.1.71\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage-local-only\",\"slug\":\"delegated-hatching-sundae\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01CadtBkbtEVCQ7bwK5ACFPL\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Write-Tests Command\\n     2→\\n     3→Create the E2E agent runner only — no unit tests, no new test scenarios. The runner registers the agent with the E2E framework so existing `ForEachAgent` tests can exercise it. Uses the implementation one-pager (`AGENT.md`) and the existing E2E test infrastructure.\\n     4→\\n     5→## Prerequisites\\n     6→\\n     7→- The research command's one-pager at `cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_PACKAGE/AGENT.md`\\n     8→- If no one-pager exists, ask the user for: binary name, prompt CLI flags, interactive mode support, and hook event names\\n     9→\\n    10→## Procedure\\n    11→\\n    12→### Step 1: Read E2E Test Infrastructure\\n    13→\\n    14→Read these files to understand the existing test patterns.\\n    15→\\n    16→**Most critical:** Focus on items 3 (`agent.go` — the interface you must implement) and read one existing agent implementation (e.g., `e2e/agents/claude.go`) as a reference. Skim the rest for context.\\n    17→\\n    18→1. `e2e/tests/main_test.go` — `TestMain` builds the CLI binary (via `entire.BinPath()`), runs preflight checks for required binaries (git, tmux, agent CLIs), sets up artifact directories, and configures env\\n    19→2. `e2e/testutil/repo.go` — `RepoState` struct (holds agent, dir, artifact dir, head/checkpoint refs), `SetupRepo` (creates temp git repo, runs `entire enable`, patches settings), `ForEachAgent` (runs a test per registered agent with repo setup, concurrency gating, and timeout scaling)\\n    20→3. `e2e/agents/agent.go` — `Agent` interface (`Name`, `Binary`, `EntireAgent`, `PromptPattern`, `TimeoutMultiplier`, `RunPrompt`, `StartSession`, `Bootstrap`, `IsTransientError`), `Register()` for agent self-registration in `init()`, `RegisterGate()` for concurrency limits, `AcquireSlot`/`ReleaseSlot` for gating\\n    21→4. `e2e/agents/tmux.go` — `TmuxSession` for interactive PTY-based tests: `NewTmuxSession`, `Send`, `SendKeys`, `WaitFor` (with settle-time logic), `Capture`, `Close`\\n    22→5. `e2e/testutil/assertions.go` — Rich assertion helpers: `AssertFileExists`, `WaitForFileExists`, `AssertNewCommits`, `WaitForCheckpoint`, `AssertCheckpointAdvanced`, `AssertHasCheckpointTrailer`, `AssertCheckpointExists`, `AssertCommitLinkedToCheckpoint`, `AssertCheckpointMetadataComplete`, `ValidateCheckpointDeep`, and many more\\n    23→6. `e2e/testutil/metadata.go` — `CheckpointMetadata`, `SessionMetadata`, `TokenUsage`, `Attribution`, `SessionRef` types; `CheckpointPath()` helper for sharded directory layout\\n    24→7. `e2e/entire/entire.go` — CLI wrapper: `BinPath()` (builds from source or uses `E2E_ENTIRE_BIN`), `Enable`, `Disable`, `RewindList`, `Rewind`, `RewindLogsOnly`, `Explain`, `ExplainGenerate`, `ExplainCommit`, `Resume`\\n    25→8. `e2e/testutil/artifacts.go` — Automatic artifact capture via `t.Cleanup`: `CaptureArtifacts` saves git-log, git-tree, checkpoint metadata, entire logs, and tmux pane content\\n    26→\\n    27→### Step 2: Read Existing E2E Test Scenarios\\n    28→\\n    29→Run `Glob(\\\"e2e/tests/*_test.go\\\")` to find all existing test files. Read a few to understand the patterns:\\n    30→- How tests use `testutil.ForEachAgent` with a timeout and callback `func(t, s, ctx)`\\n    31→- How prompts are written inline (no separate prompt template file)\\n    32→- How `s.RunPrompt`, `s.Git`, `s.StartSession`, `s.WaitFor`, `s.Send` are used\\n    33→- How assertions validate checkpoints, rewind, metadata, etc.\\n    34→\\n    35→### Step 3: Read Checkpoint Scenarios Doc\\n    36→\\n    37→Read `docs/architecture/checkpoint-scenarios.md` for the state machine and scenarios the tests should cover.\\n    38→\\n    39→### Step 4: Create Agent Implementation\\n    40→\\n    41→Read `cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_PACKAGE/AGENT.md` (the one-pager from the research phase) for all agent-specific information:\\n    42→- Binary name → \\\"Binary\\\" section\\n    43→- Prompt flags → \\\"CLI Flags\\\" section\\n    44→- Interactive mode → \\\"CLI Flags\\\" section\\n    45→- Transient error patterns → \\\"Gaps & Limitations\\\" section (use defaults if not listed)\\n    46→- Bootstrap setup → \\\"Config Preservation\\\" section\\n    47→\\n    48→**If something is missing from the one-pager**, you may search external docs — but update `AGENT.md` with anything new you discover.\\n    49→\\n    50→Add a new `Agent` implementation in `e2e/agents/${agent_slug}.go`:\\n    51→\\n    52→**Pattern to follow** (based on existing implementations like `claude.go`, `gemini.go`, `opencode.go`):\\n    53→\\n    54→```go\\n    55→package agents\\n    56→\\n    57→import (\\n    58→\\t\\\"context\\\"\\n    59→\\t\\\"errors\\\"\\n    60→\\t\\\"fmt\\\"\\n    61→\\t\\\"os\\\"\\n    62→\\t\\\"os/exec\\\"\\n    63→\\t\\\"strings\\\"\\n    64→\\t\\\"syscall\\\"\\n    65→\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n    66→)\\n    67→\\n    68→func init() {\\n    69→\\tif env := os.Getenv(\\\"E2E_AGENT\\\"); env != \\\"\\\" && env != \\\"${agent-slug}\\\" {\\n    70→\\t\\treturn\\n    71→\\t}\\n    72→\\tRegister(&${AgentName}{})\\n    73→\\t// Optional: limit concurrency for rate-limited agents\\n    74→\\t// RegisterGate(\\\"${agent-slug}\\\", 1)\\n    75→}\\n    76→\\n    77→type ${AgentName} struct{}\\n    78→\\n    79→func (a *${AgentName}) Name() string               { return \\\"${agent-slug}\\\" }\\n    80→func (a *${AgentName}) Binary() string             { return \\\"${binary-name}\\\" }\\n    81→func (a *${AgentName}) EntireAgent() string        { return \\\"${entire-agent-name}\\\" }\\n    82→func (a *${AgentName}) PromptPattern() string      { return `${prompt-regex}` }\\n    83→func (a *${AgentName}) TimeoutMultiplier() float64 { return 1.0 }\\n    84→\\n    85→func (a *${AgentName}) Bootstrap() error {\\n    86→\\t// CI-specific setup: auth config, API key injection, warmup, etc.\\n    87→\\t// Must be idempotent. Called once before any tests run.\\n    88→\\treturn nil\\n    89→}\\n    90→\\n    91→func (a *${AgentName}) IsTransientError(out Output, err error) bool {\\n    92→\\tif err == nil {\\n    93→\\t\\treturn false\\n    94→\\t}\\n    95→\\tcombined := out.Stdout + out.Stderr\\n    96→\\tfor _, p := range []string{\\\"overloaded\\\", \\\"rate limit\\\", \\\"503\\\", \\\"529\\\"} {\\n    97→\\t\\tif strings.Contains(combined, p) {\\n    98→\\t\\t\\treturn true\\n    99→\\t\\t}\\n   100→\\t}\\n   101→\\treturn false\\n   102→}\\n   103→\\n   104→func (a *${AgentName}) RunPrompt(ctx context.Context, dir string, prompt string, opts ...Option) (Output, error) {\\n   105→\\tcfg := &runConfig{}\\n   106→\\tfor _, o := range opts {\\n   107→\\t\\to(cfg)\\n   108→\\t}\\n   109→\\n   110→\\targs := []string{/* agent CLI flags for non-interactive prompt execution */}\\n   111→\\tcmd := exec.CommandContext(ctx, a.Binary(), args...)\\n   112→\\tcmd.Dir = dir\\n   113→\\tcmd.Env = append(os.Environ(), \\\"ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=0\\\")\\n   114→\\tcmd.SysProcAttr = &syscall.SysProcAttr{Setpgid: true}\\n   115→\\tcmd.Cancel = func() error {\\n   116→\\t\\treturn syscall.Kill(-cmd.Process.Pid, syscall.SIGKILL)\\n   117→\\t}\\n   118→\\n   119→\\tvar stdout, stderr strings.Builder\\n   120→\\tcmd.Stdout = &stdout\\n   121→\\tcmd.Stderr = &stderr\\n   122→\\n   123→\\terr := cmd.Run()\\n   124→\\texitCode := 0\\n   125→\\tif err != nil {\\n   126→\\t\\texitErr := &exec.ExitError{}\\n   127→\\t\\tif errors.As(err, &exitErr) {\\n   128→\\t\\t\\texitCode = exitErr.ExitCode()\\n   129→\\t\\t} else {\\n   130→\\t\\t\\texitCode = -1\\n   131→\\t\\t}\\n   132→\\t}\\n   133→\\n   134→\\treturn Output{\\n   135→\\t\\tCommand:  a.Binary() + \\\" \\\" + strings.Join(args, \\\" \\\"),\\n   136→\\t\\tStdout:   stdout.String(),\\n   137→\\t\\tStderr:   stderr.String(),\\n   138→\\t\\tExitCode: exitCode,\\n   139→\\t}, err\\n   140→}\\n   141→\\n   142→func (a *${AgentName}) StartSession(ctx context.Context, dir string) (Session, error) {\\n   143→\\t// Use NewTmuxSession for interactive PTY support.\\n   144→\\t// Return nil if agent doesn't support interactive mode.\\n   145→\\tname := fmt.Sprintf(\\\"${agent-slug}-test-%d\\\", time.Now().UnixNano())\\n   146→\\ts, err := NewTmuxSession(name, dir, nil, a.Binary(), /* interactive args */)\\n   147→\\tif err != nil {\\n   148→\\t\\treturn nil, err\\n   149→\\t}\\n   150→\\treturn s, nil\\n   151→}\\n   152→```\\n   153→\\n   154→Key implementation details:\\n   155→- Self-register in `init()` with `Register()`, gated by `E2E_AGENT` env var\\n   156→- Use `RegisterGate(\\\"name\\\", N)` if the agent's API has strict rate limits (e.g., Gemini uses gate of 1)\\n   157→- `Bootstrap()` handles CI-specific one-time setup (auth config, API key injection)\\n   158→- `IsTransientError()` identifies retryable API failures — `RepoState.RunPrompt` retries once on transient errors\\n   159→- `RunPrompt()` uses `exec.CommandContext` with `Setpgid: true` and process-group kill for clean cancellation\\n   160→- `StartSession()` uses `NewTmuxSession` for interactive PTY tests; return `nil` if interactive mode isn't supported\\n   161→- Use `AGENT.md` (the one-pager) for CLI flags, prompt passing mechanism, and env vars\\n   162→\\n   163→### Step 5: Update SetupRepo (if needed)\\n   164→\\n   165→Check if `testutil.SetupRepo` in `e2e/testutil/repo.go` needs agent-specific configuration. Look for the existing `if agent.Name() == \\\"opencode\\\"` block as an example:\\n   166→\\n   167→- Agent-specific config files that must exist before `entire enable`\\n   168→- Permission or auth config files\\n   169→- Environment variables needed for hook testing\\n   170→\\n   171→If no special setup is needed, skip this step.\\n   172→\\n   173→### Step 6: Verify\\n   174→\\n   175→After writing the runner code:\\n   176→\\n   177→1. **Lint check**: `mise run lint` — ensure no lint errors\\n   178→2. **Compile check**: `go test -c -tags=e2e ./e2e/tests` — compile-only with the build tag to verify the runner compiles and registers\\n   179→3. **Verify registration**: The runner's `init()` calls `Register()` and will be picked up by `ForEachAgent` in existing tests\\n   180→4. **Add mise task**: Remind the user that E2E tests are run via `mise run test:e2e --agent ${agent_slug}` and to update CI workflows if needed\\n   181→5. **Next step**: The implement phase will run E2E tests against this runner — that's where failures are diagnosed and fixed\\n   182→\\n   183→### Step 7: Commit\\n   184→\\n   185→Use `/commit` to commit all files.\\n   186→\\n   187→## Key Conventions\\n   188→\\n   189→- **Build tag**: All E2E test files must have `//go:build e2e` as the first line\\n   190→- **Package**: `package tests` for test files in `e2e/tests/`; `package agents` for agent implementations in `e2e/agents/`\\n   191→- **Parallel**: `ForEachAgent` handles parallelism — do not call `t.Parallel()` inside the callback\\n   192→- **Repo setup**: `ForEachAgent` calls `SetupRepo` automatically — do not call it manually\\n   193→- **Prompts**: Write prompts inline in the test. Include \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prevent agent stalling\\n   194→- **Assertions**: Use helpers from `e2e/testutil/assertions.go` — see `AssertFileExists`, `WaitForCheckpoint`, `AssertCommitLinkedToCheckpoint`, `ValidateCheckpointDeep`, etc.\\n   195→- **CLI operations**: Use the `e2e/entire` package (`entire.Enable`, `entire.RewindList`, `entire.Rewind`, etc.) — never call the binary via raw `exec.Command`\\n   196→- **No hardcoded paths**: Use `s.Dir` for repo paths, `s.ArtifactDir` for artifacts\\n   197→- **Console logging**: All operations through `s.RunPrompt`, `s.Git`, `s.Send`, `s.WaitFor` are automatically logged to `console.log`\\n   198→- **Transient errors**: `s.RunPrompt` auto-retries once on transient API errors via `IsTransientError`\\n   199→- **Interactive tests**: Use `s.StartSession`, `s.Send`, `s.WaitFor` — tmux pane is auto-captured in artifacts\\n   200→- **Run commands**: `mise run test:e2e --agent ${slug} TestName` — see `e2e/README.md` for all options\\n   201→- **E2E tests are run during the implement phase**: This phase only creates the runner. The implement phase runs E2E tests at each tier to drive development.\\n   202→- **Debugging failures**: If tests fail during the implement phase, use `/debug-e2e` with the artifact directory to diagnose CLI-level issues (hooks, checkpoints, session phases, attribution)\\n   203→\\n   204→## Output\\n   205→\\n   206→Summarize what was created/modified:\\n   207→- Files added or modified\\n   208→- New agent runner details (how it invokes the agent, auth setup, concurrency gate)\\n   209→- Confirmation that the runner compiles and registers with the E2E framework\\n   210→- Reminder to update `mise.toml` and CI workflows\\n   211→- Note that the implement phase will run E2E tests against this runner\\n   212→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"f7fdf2c3-90d6-4ab9-8340-1b5181fb915f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:45:30.103Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a4f91b1ff72fb48e5\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01VEiM5bmK9sCnTqaXtpfURh\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01CHSGpd9mgfnLtAUuoyLCRa\",\"uuid\":\"9e25acaf-d11d-425f-9599-447b399638a0\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:45:30.110Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"9e25acaf-d11d-425f-9599-447b399638a0\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"00468b34-359e-43a2-b0bb-30677f1aee5e\",\"version\":\"2.1.71\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage-local-only\",\"slug\":\"delegated-hatching-sundae\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:45:31.621Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01QXRiAjDUWgruxjyNaU3ZJu\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01W4zPpQUwh5vzAoYMF8vYmC\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/.claude/skills/agent-integration/implementer.md\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":4074,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":57590,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":4074,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":18,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYno6v9pc89XjHc8ZhXDG\",\"uuid\":\"f29fe256-e281-4ffc-9b54-4267c633854c\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a4f91b1ff72fb48e5\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01VEiM5bmK9sCnTqaXtpfURh\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01CHSGpd9mgfnLtAUuoyLCRa\",\"uuid\":\"f755bd5b-f313-4635-8b98-02b2941d6beb\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:45:31.621Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"f755bd5b-f313-4635-8b98-02b2941d6beb\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"00468b34-359e-43a2-b0bb-30677f1aee5e\",\"version\":\"2.1.71\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage-local-only\",\"slug\":\"delegated-hatching-sundae\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01W4zPpQUwh5vzAoYMF8vYmC\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Implement Command\\n     2→\\n     3→Build the agent Go package using strict E2E-first TDD. Unit tests are written ONLY after all E2E tests pass.\\n     4→\\n     5→## Prerequisites\\n     6→\\n     7→- The research command's one-pager at `cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_PACKAGE/AGENT.md`\\n     8→- The E2E test runner already added (from `write-tests` command)\\n     9→- If no one-pager exists, read the agent's docs and ask the user about hook events, transcript format, and config\\n    10→\\n    11→## Core Principle: E2E-First TDD\\n    12→\\n    13→1. **E2E tests are the spec.** The existing `ForEachAgent` test scenarios define \\\"working\\\". You implement until they pass.\\n    14→2. **Watch it fail first.** Every E2E tier starts by running the test and observing the failure. If you haven't seen the failure, you don't understand what needs fixing.\\n    15→3. **Minimum viable fix.** At each failure, implement only the code needed to make that specific assertion pass. Don't anticipate future tiers.\\n    16→4. **`/debug-e2e` is your debugger.** When an E2E test fails, use the artifact directory with `/debug-e2e` before guessing at fixes.\\n    17→5. **No unit tests during Steps 4-13.** Unit tests are written in Step 14 after all E2E tiers pass, using real data from E2E runs as golden fixtures.\\n    18→6. **Format and lint, don't unit test.** Between E2E tiers, run `mise run fmt && mise run lint` to keep code clean. Any earlier `mise run test` invocations (e.g., in Step 3) are strictly compile-only sanity checks — no `mise run test` between E2E tiers (Steps 4-13).\\n    19→7. **If you didn't watch it fail, you don't know if it tests the right thing.**\\n    20→\\n    21→**Do NOT write unit tests during Steps 4-13.** All test writing is consolidated in Step 14.\\n    22→\\n    23→## Procedure\\n    24→\\n    25→### Step 1: Read Implementation Guide\\n    26→\\n    27→Read these files thoroughly before writing any code:\\n    28→\\n    29→1. `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — Authoritative implementation guide with code templates. Read thoroughly.\\n    30→2. `docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md` — Validation criteria for completeness.\\n    31→3. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go` — Read to find the exact `Agent` interface and all optional interfaces.\\n    32→4. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/event.go` — Read to find `EventType` constants and shared parsing helpers.\\n    33→\\n    34→### Step 2: Read Reference Implementation\\n    35→\\n    36→Read `cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_PACKAGE/AGENT.md` (the one-pager from the research phase) for the agent's hook mechanism, transcript format, and config structure.\\n    37→\\n    38→Run `Glob(\\\"cmd/entire/cli/agent/*/\\\")` to find all existing agent packages. Check the one-pager's \\\"Hook Mechanism\\\" and \\\"Gaps & Limitations\\\" sections to pick the best reference — choose an agent with a similar hook mechanism to your target. Read all `*.go` files (skip `*_test.go` on first pass) in the chosen reference.\\n    39→\\n    40→### Step 3: Create Bare-Minimum Compiling Package\\n    41→\\n    42→Create the agent package directory and stub out every required interface method so the project compiles.\\n    43→\\n    44→```\\n    45→cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_PACKAGE/\\n    46→```\\n    47→\\n    48→**What to create:**\\n    49→\\n    50→1. **`${AGENT_PACKAGE}.go`** — Struct definition, `init()` with `agent.Register(agent.AgentName(\\\"$AGENT_KEY\\\"), New)`, and stub implementations for every method in the `Agent` interface — refer to `agent.go` from Step 1. Include `HookSupport` methods in `lifecycle.go` and `hooks.go`.\\n    51→2. **`types.go`** — Hook input struct(s) with JSON tags matching the one-pager's \\\"Hook input (stdin JSON)\\\" section.\\n    52→3. **`lifecycle.go`** — Stub `ParseHookEvent()` that returns `nil, nil` for all inputs. Use the one-pager's \\\"Hook names\\\" table for the native hook name → Entire EventType mapping.\\n    53→4. **`hooks.go`** — Stub `InstallHooks()`, `UninstallHooks()`, `AreHooksInstalled()` that return nil/false. Use the one-pager's \\\"Config file\\\" and \\\"Hook registration\\\" sections for the config path and format.\\n    54→5. **`transcript.go`** — Stub `TranscriptAnalyzer` methods if the one-pager's \\\"Transcript\\\" section indicates the agent supports transcript analysis. Use the one-pager for transcript location and format.\\n    55→\\n    56→**Wire up blank imports:**\\n    57→\\n    58→- Ensure the blank import `_ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_PACKAGE\\\"` exists in `cmd/entire/cli/hooks_cmd.go`\\n    59→\\n    60→**Verify compilation (compile-only sanity check, not unit-test-driven development):**\\n    61→\\n    62→```bash\\n    63→mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test\\n    64→```\\n    65→\\n    66→Everything must compile and pass existing tests before proceeding. Fix any issues.\\n    67→\\n    68→**Commit:** Use `/commit` to commit all files. Skip if no files changed.\\n    69→\\n    70→**Standing instruction for Steps 4-12:** If you need agent-specific information (hook format, transcript location, config structure), check `AGENT.md` first. If `AGENT.md` doesn't cover what you need, you may search external docs — but always update `AGENT.md` with anything new you discover so future steps don't need to re-search.\\n    71→\\n    72→### Step 4: E2E Tier 1 — `TestHumanOnlyChangesAndCommits`\\n    73→\\n    74→This test requires no agent prompts — it only exercises hooks, so it's the fastest feedback loop.\\n    75→\\n    76→**What it exercises:**\\n    77→- `InstallHooks()` — real hook installation in the agent's config\\n    78→- `AreHooksInstalled()` — detection that hooks are present\\n    79→- `ParseHookEvent()` — at minimum, the event types needed for session start and turn end (see `EventType` constants in `event.go`)\\n    80→- Basic hook invocation flow (the test calls hooks directly via the CLI)\\n    81→\\n    82→**Cycle:**\\n    83→\\n    84→1. Run: `mise run test:e2e --agent $AGENT_SLUG TestHumanOnlyChangesAndCommits`\\n    85→2. **Watch it fail** — read the failure output carefully\\n    86→3. If there are artifact dirs, use `/debug-e2e {artifact-dir}` to understand what happened\\n    87→4. Implement the minimum code to fix the first failure\\n    88→5. Repeat until the test passes\\n    89→\\n    90→Run: `mise run fmt && mise run lint`\\n    91→\\n    92→**Commit:** Use `/commit` to commit all files. Skip if no files changed.\\n    93→\\n    94→### Step 5: E2E Tier 2 — `TestSingleSessionManualCommit`\\n    95→\\n    96→The foundational test. This exercises the full agent lifecycle: start session → agent prompt → agent produces files → user commits → session ends.\\n    97→\\n    98→**What it exercises:**\\n    99→- Complete `ParseHookEvent()` for all lifecycle event types from `event.go`. Use the one-pager's hook mapping table to translate native hook names to `EventType` constants.\\n   100→- `GetSessionDir` / `ResolveSessionFile` — finding the agent's session/transcript files\\n   101→- `ReadTranscript` / `ChunkTranscript` / `ReassembleTranscript` — reading native transcript format\\n   102→- `TranscriptAnalyzer` methods (see `agent.go` for current method signatures)\\n   103→\\n   104→**Cycle:**\\n   105→\\n   106→1. Run: `mise run test:e2e --agent $AGENT_SLUG TestSingleSessionManualCommit`\\n   107→2. **Watch it fail** — read the failure output carefully\\n   108→3. Use `/debug-e2e {artifact-dir}` to understand what happened\\n   109→4. Implement the minimum code to fix the first failure\\n   110→5. Repeat until the test passes\\n   111→\\n   112→Run: `mise run fmt && mise run lint`\\n   113→\\n   114→**Commit:** Use `/commit` to commit all files. Skip if no files changed.\\n   115→\\n   116→### Step 6: E2E Tier 2b — `TestCheckpointMetadataDeepValidation`\\n   117→\\n   118→Validates transcript quality: JSONL validity, content hash correctness, prompt extraction accuracy.\\n   119→\\n   120→**What it exercises:**\\n   121→- Transcript content stored at checkpoints is valid JSONL\\n   122→- Content hash matches the stored transcript\\n   123→- User prompts are correctly extracted\\n   124→- Metadata fields are populated\\n   125→\\n   126→**Cycle:**\\n   127→\\n   128→1. Run: `mise run test:e2e --agent $AGENT_SLUG TestCheckpointMetadataDeepValidation`\\n   129→2. **Watch it fail** — this test often exposes subtle transcript formatting bugs\\n   130→3. Use `/debug-e2e {artifact-dir}` on any failures\\n   131→4. Fix and repeat\\n   132→\\n   133→Run: `mise run fmt && mise run lint`\\n   134→\\n   135→**Commit:** Use `/commit` to commit all files. Skip if no files changed.\\n   136→\\n   137→### Step 7: E2E Tier 3 — `TestSingleSessionAgentCommitInTurn`\\n   138→\\n   139→Agent creates files and commits them within a single prompt turn. Tests the in-turn commit path.\\n   140→\\n   141→**What it exercises:**\\n   142→- Hook events firing during an agent's commit (post-commit hooks while agent is active)\\n   143→- Checkpoint creation when agent commits mid-turn\\n   144→- Usually no new agent-specific code needed — this tests the strategy's handling of agent commits\\n   145→\\n   146→**Cycle:**\\n   147→\\n   148→1. Run: `mise run test:e2e --agent $AGENT_SLUG TestSingleSessionAgentCommitInTurn`\\n   149→2. **Watch it fail** — use `/debug-e2e {artifact-dir}` on failures\\n   150→3. Fix and repeat — if the agent doesn't support committing, skip this test\\n   151→\\n   152→Run: `mise run fmt && mise run lint`\\n   153→\\n   154→**Commit:** Use `/commit` to commit all files. Skip if no files changed.\\n   155→\\n   156→### Step 8: E2E Tier 4 — Multi-Session Tests\\n   157→\\n   158→Run these tests to validate multi-session behavior:\\n   159→\\n   160→- `TestMultiSessionManualCommit` — Two sessions, both produce files, user commits\\n   161→- `TestMultiSessionSequential` — Sessions run one after another\\n   162→- `TestEndedSessionUserCommitsAfterExit` — User commits after session ends\\n   163→\\n   164→**Cycle (for each test):**\\n   165→\\n   166→1. Run: `mise run test:e2e --agent $AGENT_SLUG TestMultiSessionManualCommit`\\n   167→2. **Watch it fail** — use `/debug-e2e {artifact-dir}` on failures\\n   168→3. Fix and repeat\\n   169→4. Move to next test\\n   170→\\n   171→These tests rarely need new agent code — they exercise the strategy layer.\\n   172→\\n   173→Run: `mise run fmt && mise run lint`\\n   174→\\n   175→**Commit:** Use `/commit` to commit all files. Skip if no files changed.\\n   176→\\n   177→### Step 9: E2E Tier 5 — File Operation Edge Cases\\n   178→\\n   179→Run these tests for file operation correctness:\\n   180→\\n   181→- `TestModifyExistingTrackedFile` — Agent modifies (not creates) a file\\n   182→- `TestUserSplitsAgentChanges` — User stages only some of the agent's changes\\n   183→- `TestDeletedFilesCommitDeletion` — Agent deletes a file, user commits the deletion\\n   184→- `TestMixedNewAndModifiedFiles` — Agent both creates and modifies files\\n   185→\\n   186→**Cycle:** Same as above — run each test, **watch it fail**, use `/debug-e2e` on failures, fix, repeat.\\n   187→\\n   188→Run: `mise run fmt && mise run lint`\\n   189→\\n   190→**Commit:** Use `/commit` to commit all files. Skip if no files changed.\\n   191→\\n   192→### Step 10: Optional Interfaces\\n   193→\\n   194→Read `cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go` for all optional interfaces. For each one the one-pager's \\\"Gaps & Limitations\\\" or \\\"Transcript\\\" sections suggest is feasible:\\n   195→\\n   196→- **`TranscriptPreparer`** — If the agent needs pre-processing before transcript storage\\n   197→- **`TokenCalculator`** — If the agent provides token usage data\\n   198→- **`SubagentAwareExtractor`** — If the agent has subagent/tool-use patterns\\n   199→\\n   200→For each optional interface:\\n   201→\\n   202→1. Implement the methods based on `AGENT.md` and reference implementation\\n   203→2. Run relevant E2E tests to verify integration (e.g., `TestCheckpointMetadataDeepValidation` for transcript methods)\\n   204→\\n   205→Run: `mise run fmt && mise run lint`\\n   206→\\n   207→**Commit:** Use `/commit` to commit all files. Skip if no files changed.\\n   208→\\n   209→### Step 11: E2E Tier 6 — Interactive and Rewind Tests\\n   210→\\n   211→Run these if the agent supports interactive multi-step sessions:\\n   212→\\n   213→- `TestInteractiveMultiStep` — Multiple prompts in one session\\n   214→- `TestRewindPreCommit` — Rewind to a checkpoint before committing\\n   215→- `TestRewindAfterCommit` — Rewind to a checkpoint after committing\\n   216→- `TestRewindMultipleFiles` — Rewind with multiple files changed\\n   217→\\n   218→**Cycle:** Same pattern — run, **watch it fail**, `/debug-e2e` on failures, fix, repeat.\\n   219→\\n   220→Run: `mise run fmt && mise run lint`\\n   221→\\n   222→**Commit:** Use `/commit` to commit all files. Skip if no files changed.\\n   223→\\n   224→### Step 12: E2E Tier 7 — Complex Scenarios\\n   225→\\n   226→Run the remaining edge case and stress tests:\\n   227→\\n   228→- `TestPartialCommitStashNewPrompt` — Partial commit, stash, new prompt\\n   229→- `TestStashSecondPromptUnstashCommitAll` — Stash workflow across prompts\\n   230→- `TestRapidSequentialCommits` — Multiple commits in quick succession\\n   231→- `TestAgentContinuesAfterCommit` — Agent keeps working after a commit\\n   232→- `TestSubagentCommitFlow` — If the agent has subagent support\\n   233→- `TestSingleSessionSubagentCommitInTurn` — Subagent commits during a turn\\n   234→\\n   235→**Cycle:** Same pattern — **watch it fail**, fix, repeat. Many of these require no new agent code — they exercise strategy-layer behavior.\\n   236→\\n   237→Run: `mise run fmt && mise run lint`\\n   238→\\n   239→**Commit:** Use `/commit` to commit all files. Skip if no files changed.\\n   240→\\n   241→### Step 13: Full E2E Suite Pass\\n   242→\\n   243→Run the complete E2E suite for the agent to catch any regressions or tests that were skipped in earlier tiers:\\n   244→\\n   245→```bash\\n   246→mise run test:e2e --agent $AGENT_SLUG\\n   247→```\\n   248→\\n   249→This runs every `ForEachAgent` test, not just the ones targeted in Steps 4-12.\\n   250→\\n   251→**Important: E2E tests can be flaky when run all at once.** Do NOT run them in parallel — always use sequential execution. If some tests fail when running the full suite, re-run each failing test individually before investigating:\\n   252→\\n   253→```bash\\n   254→mise run test:e2e --agent $AGENT_SLUG TestFailingTestName\\n   255→```\\n   256→\\n   257→If a test passes when run individually but fails in the full suite, it's a flaky failure — not a real error. Only investigate failures that reproduce consistently when run in isolation.\\n   258→\\n   259→Fix any real failures before proceeding — the same cycle applies: read the failure, use `/debug-e2e {artifact-dir}`, implement the minimum fix, re-run.\\n   260→\\n   261→All E2E tests must pass before writing unit tests.\\n   262→\\n   263→### Step 14: Write Unit Tests\\n   264→\\n   265→Now that all E2E tiers pass, write unit tests to lock in behavior. Use real data from E2E runs (captured JSON payloads, transcript snippets, config file contents) as golden fixtures.\\n   266→\\n   267→**Test files to create:**\\n   268→\\n   269→1. **`hooks_test.go`** — Test `InstallHooks` (creates config, idempotent), `UninstallHooks` (removes hooks), `AreHooksInstalled` (detects presence). Use a temp directory to avoid touching real config.\\n   270→\\n   271→2. **`lifecycle_test.go`** — Test `ParseHookEvent` for all event types. Use actual JSON payloads from E2E artifacts or `AGENT.md` examples. Test every `EventType` mapping, nil returns for unknown hook names, pass-through hooks, empty input, and malformed JSON. **Important:** Test against `EventType` constants from `event.go`, not native hook names — the agent's native hook verbs (e.g., \\\"stop\\\") map to normalized EventTypes (e.g., `TurnEnd`).\\n   272→\\n   273→3. **`types_test.go`** — Test hook input struct parsing with actual JSON payloads from E2E artifacts or `AGENT.md` examples.\\n   274→\\n   275→4. **`transcript_test.go`** — Test `ReadTranscript`, `ChunkTranscript`, `ReassembleTranscript` with sample data in the agent's native format. Test all `TranscriptAnalyzer` methods (from `agent.go`) if implemented. Use transcript snippets from E2E artifact directories as golden test data.\\n   276→\\n   277→5. **`${AGENT_PACKAGE}_test.go`** — Test agent constructor (`New`), `Name()`, `AgentName()`, and any other agent-level methods. Verify the agent satisfies all expected interfaces using compile-time checks (`var _ agent.Agent = (*${AgentType})(nil)`).\\n   278→\\n   279→**Where to find golden test data:**\\n   280→\\n   281→- E2E artifact directories contain captured transcripts, hook payloads, and config files\\n   282→- `AGENT.md` has example JSON payloads in the \\\"Hook input\\\" sections\\n   283→- The agent's actual config file format from E2E test repos\\n   284→\\n   285→Run: `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test`\\n   286→\\n   287→**Commit:** Use `/commit` to commit all files. Skip if no files changed.\\n   288→\\n   289→### Step 15: Verify Registration\\n   290→\\n   291→Verify that registration from Step 3 is correct and complete:\\n   292→\\n   293→1. The `init()` function in `${AGENT_PACKAGE}.go` calls `agent.Register(agent.AgentName(\\\"$AGENT_KEY\\\"), New)`\\n   294→2. The blank import in `cmd/entire/cli/hooks_cmd.go` is present\\n   295→3. Run the full test suite: `mise run test:ci`\\n   296→\\n   297→### Step 16: Final Validation\\n   298→\\n   299→Run the complete validation:\\n   300→\\n   301→```bash\\n   302→mise run fmt      # Format\\n   303→mise run lint     # Lint\\n   304→mise run test:ci  # All tests (unit + integration)\\n   305→```\\n   306→\\n   307→Check against the integration checklist (`docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md`):\\n   308→\\n   309→- [ ] Full transcript stored at every checkpoint\\n   310→- [ ] Native format preserved\\n   311→- [ ] All mappable hook events implemented\\n   312→- [ ] Session storage working\\n   313→- [ ] Hook installation/uninstallation working\\n   314→- [ ] Tests pass with `t.Parallel()`\\n   315→\\n   316→**Commit:** Use `/commit` to commit all files. Skip if no files changed.\\n   317→\\n   318→## E2E Debugging Protocol\\n   319→\\n   320→At every E2E failure, follow this protocol:\\n   321→\\n   322→1. **Read the test output** — the assertion message often tells you exactly what's wrong\\n   323→2. **Find the artifact directory** — E2E tests save artifacts (logs, transcripts, git state) to a temp dir printed in the output\\n   324→3. **Run `/debug-e2e {artifact-dir}`** — this skill analyzes artifacts and diagnoses the root cause\\n   325→4. **Implement the minimum fix** — don't over-engineer; fix only what the test demands\\n   326→5. **Re-run the failing test** — not the whole suite, just the one test\\n   327→\\n   328→## Key Patterns to Follow\\n   329→\\n   330→- **Use `agent.ReadAndParseHookInput[T]`** for parsing hook stdin JSON\\n   331→- **Use `paths.WorktreeRoot()`** not `os.Getwd()` for git-relative paths\\n   332→- **Preserve unknown config keys** when modifying agent config files (don't clobber user settings)\\n   333→- **Use `logging.Debug/Info/Warn/Error`** for internal logging, not `fmt.Print`\\n   334→- **Keep interface implementations minimal** — only implement what's needed\\n   335→- **Follow Go idioms** from `.golangci.yml` — check before writing code\\n   336→\\n   337→## Output\\n   338→\\n   339→Summarize what was implemented:\\n   340→- Package directory and files created\\n   341→- Interfaces implemented (core + optional)\\n   342→- Hook names registered\\n   343→- E2E tiers passing (list which E2E tests pass)\\n   344→- Unit test coverage (number of test functions, what they cover — written in Step 14)\\n   345→- Any gaps or TODOs remaining\\n   346→- Commands to run full validation\\n   347→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"ed6c8ce8-8007-4a41-8e46-91a2287b473b\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:45:31.631Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a4f91b1ff72fb48e5\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01VEiM5bmK9sCnTqaXtpfURh\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01CHSGpd9mgfnLtAUuoyLCRa\",\"uuid\":\"2fd1c8ec-b4b8-46dc-bc81-f260b2f5bac4\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:45:31.632Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"2fd1c8ec-b4b8-46dc-bc81-f260b2f5bac4\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"00468b34-359e-43a2-b0bb-30677f1aee5e\",\"version\":\"2.1.71\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage-local-only\",\"slug\":\"delegated-hatching-sundae\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:45:33.780Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_016TtwSrx1FE8mwLK6E39cVD\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01JrbmggqX9Yx5EUMc8vHBRM\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/.claude/skills/e2e-triage/SKILL.md\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":6043,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":61664,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":6043,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYno72hyATfY9EVSATP6j\",\"uuid\":\"6cd3e7ae-7843-4f81-8d11-105137598f51\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a4f91b1ff72fb48e5\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01VEiM5bmK9sCnTqaXtpfURh\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01CHSGpd9mgfnLtAUuoyLCRa\",\"uuid\":\"6575c29b-aabf-49b4-8a18-d227c5e4993d\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:45:33.780Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"6575c29b-aabf-49b4-8a18-d227c5e4993d\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"00468b34-359e-43a2-b0bb-30677f1aee5e\",\"version\":\"2.1.71\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage-local-only\",\"slug\":\"delegated-hatching-sundae\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01JrbmggqX9Yx5EUMc8vHBRM\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→---\\n     2→name: e2e-triage\\n     3→description: Triage E2E test failures — run locally with mise, classify flaky vs real bug. Presents findings and applies fixes in-place.\\n     4→---\\n     5→\\n     6→# E2E Triage\\n     7→\\n     8→Triage E2E test failures with **re-run verification**. Analyzes artifacts and re-runs failing tests locally to distinguish flaky from real bugs. Presents findings interactively and applies fixes directly in the working tree.\\n     9→\\n    10→---\\n    11→\\n    12→## Step L1: Parse User Input\\n    13→\\n    14→The user provides one or more of:\\n    15→- **Test name(s)** — e.g., `TestInteractiveMultiStep`\\n    16→- **`--agent <agent>`** — optional, defaults to all agents that previously failed\\n    17→- **A local artifact path** — skip straight to analysis of existing artifacts\\n    18→- **CI run reference** — triggers artifact download instead of local re-runs:\\n    19→  - `latest CI run` / `latest` — most recent failed E2E run on main\\n    20→  - A GitHub Actions run ID (numeric, e.g., `12345678`)\\n    21→  - A GitHub Actions run URL\\n    22→\\n    23→**CI artifact download:** When a CI run reference is provided, download artifacts using:\\n    24→\\n    25→```bash\\n    26→scripts/download-e2e-artifacts.sh <latest | RUN_ID | RUN_URL>\\n    27→```\\n    28→\\n    29→The script outputs the absolute artifact path as its **last line of stdout** — capture that and use it as the artifact path for analysis. After downloading, **skip Steps L2–L5** (local re-runs) and go straight to **Shared Analysis** (Step 1), since we're analyzing CI artifacts, not running tests locally.\\n    30→\\n    31→**Cost warning:** Real E2E tests consume API tokens. Before running, confirm with the user unless they provided specific test names (implying intent to run).\\n    32→\\n    33→## Step L2: First Run\\n    34→\\n    35→```bash\\n    36→mise run test:e2e --agent <agent> <TestName>\\n    37→```\\n    38→\\n    39→Capture the artifact directory from the `artifacts: <path>` output line.\\n    40→\\n    41→## Step L3: Re-run on Failure\\n    42→\\n    43→If the test **passes** on first run: report as passing, done for this test.\\n    44→\\n    45→If the test **fails**: run a **second time** with the same parameters.\\n    46→\\n    47→## Step L4: Tiebreaker (if needed)\\n    48→\\n    49→If results are **split** (1 pass, 1 fail): run a **third time** as tiebreaker.\\n    50→\\n    51→## Step L5: Collect Results\\n    52→\\n    53→For each test+agent pair, record: `(test, agent, run_1_result, run_2_result, [run_3_result])`\\n    54→\\n    55→Proceed to **Shared Analysis** (Step 1 below).\\n    56→\\n    57→---\\n    58→\\n    59→## Shared Analysis & Classification\\n    60→\\n    61→### Step 1: Analyze Each Failure\\n    62→\\n    63→For each failure, follow the **Debugging Workflow** in `.claude/skills/debug-e2e/SKILL.md` (steps 2-5: console.log → test source → entire.log → deep dive). Collect:\\n    64→- What the agent actually did (from console.log)\\n    65→- What was expected (from test source)\\n    66→- CLI-level errors or anomalies (from entire.log)\\n    67→- Repo/checkpoint state (from git-log.txt, git-tree.txt, checkpoint-metadata/)\\n    68→\\n    69→### Step 2: Classify Each Failure\\n    70→\\n    71→Use **re-run results as the primary signal**, supplemented by artifact analysis.\\n    72→\\n    73→#### Re-run signals (strongest):\\n    74→\\n    75→| Original | Re-run 1 | Re-run 2 | Classification |\\n    76→|----------|----------|----------|----------------|\\n    77→| FAIL | FAIL (same error) | FAIL (same error) | **real-bug** OR **flaky (test-bug)** — see below |\\n    78→| FAIL | PASS | PASS | **flaky** |\\n    79→| FAIL | PASS | FAIL | **flaky** (non-deterministic) |\\n    80→| FAIL | FAIL | PASS | **flaky** (non-deterministic) |\\n    81→| FAIL | FAIL (different error) | FAIL (different error) | **needs deeper analysis** — examine artifacts |\\n    82→\\n    83→**Important: Consistent failures can still be `flaky` (test-bug).** When all re-runs fail, check *where* the root cause is:\\n    84→- Root cause in `cmd/entire/cli/` → **real-bug** (product code is broken)\\n    85→- Root cause in `e2e/` (test infra, test helpers, tmux setup, env propagation) → **flaky (test-bug)** — the CLI works fine, the test is broken\\n    86→\\n    87→#### Strong `real-bug` signals (root cause must be in `cmd/entire/cli/`, not `e2e/`):\\n    88→\\n    89→- `entire.log` contains `\\\"level\\\":\\\"ERROR\\\"` or panic/stack traces from CLI code\\n    90→- Checkpoint metadata structurally corrupt (malformed JSON, missing `checkpoint_id`/`strategy`)\\n    91→- Session state file missing or malformed when expected\\n    92→- Hooks did not fire at all (no `hook invoked` log entries)\\n    93→- Shadow/metadata branch has wrong tree structure\\n    94→- Same test fails across 3+ agents with same non-timeout symptom\\n    95→- Error references CLI code (panic in `cmd/entire/cli/`)\\n    96→\\n    97→**Key question:** Is the bug in `cmd/entire/cli/` (product code) or in `e2e/` (test code)? Only the former is a `real-bug`.\\n    98→\\n    99→#### Strong `flaky` signals (unless overridden by real-bug):\\n   100→\\n   101→**Agent behavior (non-deterministic):**\\n   102→- `signal: killed` (timeout)\\n   103→- `context deadline exceeded` or `WaitForCheckpoint.*exceeded deadline`\\n   104→- Agent asked for confirmation instead of acting\\n   105→- Agent created file at wrong path / wrong name\\n   106→- Agent produced no output\\n   107→- Agent committed when it shouldn't have (or vice versa)\\n   108→- Duration near timeout limit\\n   109→\\n   110→**Test-bug (consistent failure, but root cause is in `e2e/` not `cmd/entire/cli/`):**\\n   111→- Agent \\\"Not logged in\\\" / auth errors → test env setup doesn't propagate auth credentials\\n   112→- Env vars not propagated to agent session → tmux/test harness bug\\n   113→- Error references test code (`e2e/`) not CLI code (`cmd/entire/cli/`)\\n   114→- Test helper logic errors (wrong assertions, bad globs, incorrect expected values)\\n   115→- Consistent failure BUT root cause traced to `e2e/` code, not `cmd/entire/cli/`\\n   116→- Test setup/teardown issues (missing git config, temp dir cleanup, port conflicts)\\n   117→\\n   118→#### Ambiguous cases:\\n   119→\\n   120→Read `entire.log` carefully:\\n   121→- If hooks fired correctly and metadata is valid -> lean **flaky**\\n   122→- If hooks fired but produced wrong results -> lean **real-bug**\\n   123→\\n   124→### Step 3: Cross-Agent Correlation\\n   125→\\n   126→Before acting, check correlations using re-run data:\\n   127→- Same test fails for 3+ agents, all re-runs also fail -> strong **real-bug**\\n   128→- Same test fails for multiple agents, but re-runs pass -> **flaky** (shared prompt issue)\\n   129→- One agent fails consistently, others pass -> agent-specific issue (still **real-bug** if re-runs confirm)\\n   130→\\n   131→### Step 4: Take Action\\n   132→\\n   133→Present findings interactively. **Do not** create branches, PRs, or GitHub issues.\\n   134→\\n   135→#### Present Findings Report\\n   136→\\n   137→For each test+agent pair, print a findings block:\\n   138→\\n   139→```\\n   140→## <TestName> (<agent>) — <classification>\\n   141→\\n   142→**Re-run results:** original=FAIL, rerun1=PASS, rerun2=PASS\\n   143→**Evidence:**\\n   144→- <1-2 sentence summary of what went wrong>\\n   145→- <key artifact evidence: entire.log excerpt, console.log excerpt, etc.>\\n   146→```\\n   147→\\n   148→#### For `flaky` failures: describe the proposed fix\\n   149→\\n   150→For agent-behavior flaky issues, fixes typically modify test prompts. For test-bug flaky issues, fixes target `e2e/` infrastructure code (harness setup, helpers, env propagation).\\n   151→\\n   152→```\\n   153→**Proposed fix:** <description>\\n   154→  - File: <path to test file or e2e infrastructure file>\\n   155→  - Change: <what will be modified — e.g., append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prompt, or fix env propagation in NewTmuxSession>\\n   156→```\\n   157→\\n   158→Common flaky fixes:\\n   159→- Agent asked for confirmation -> append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prompt\\n   160→- Agent wrote to wrong path -> be more explicit about paths in prompt\\n   161→- Agent committed when shouldn't -> add \\\"Do not commit\\\" to prompt\\n   162→- Checkpoint wait timeout -> increase timeout argument\\n   163→- Agent timeout (signal: killed) -> increase per-test timeout, simplify prompt\\n   164→- Auth/env not propagated -> fix test harness env setup in `e2e/` code\\n   165→- Test helper bug (wrong assertion, bad glob) -> fix test helper in `e2e/`\\n   166→- tmux session setup issue -> fix `NewTmuxSession` or session config in `e2e/`\\n   167→\\n   168→#### For `real-bug` failures: describe root cause analysis\\n   169→\\n   170→```\\n   171→**Root cause analysis:**\\n   172→  - Component: <hooks | session | checkpoint | strategy | agent>\\n   173→  - Suspected location: <file:function>\\n   174→  - Description: <what's wrong and why>\\n   175→  - Proposed fix: <what code change would address it>\\n   176→```\\n   177→\\n   178→#### Ask the user\\n   179→\\n   180→Prompt the user:\\n   181→\\n   182→> **Should I fix these?**\\n   183→> - [list of tests with classifications]\\n   184→> - You can select all, specific tests, or skip.\\n   185→\\n   186→Wait for user response before proceeding.\\n   187→\\n   188→#### Apply fixes (if user approves)\\n   189→\\n   190→For **flaky** fixes the user approved:\\n   191→1. Apply fixes directly in the working tree (no branch creation)\\n   192→2. Run static checks:\\n   193→   ```bash\\n   194→   mise run fmt && mise run lint\\n   195→   mise run test:e2e:canary   # Must pass\\n   196→   ```\\n   197→3. **Run real E2E tests to verify the fix.** Scope depends on what was changed:\\n   198→   - **Agent-specific fix** (e.g., `e2e/agents/cursor_cli.go`, one agent's config/trust/env): run the full suite for that agent only:\\n   199→     ```bash\\n   200→     mise run test:e2e --agent <agent>\\n   201→     ```\\n   202→   - **Shared test infra fix** (e.g., `e2e/agents/agent.go`, `e2e/testutil/`, `TmuxSession`, test helpers): run the full suite for all agents that failed, since the fix could affect any of them:\\n   203→     ```bash\\n   204→     mise run test:e2e --agent <agent1>\\n   205→     mise run test:e2e --agent <agent2>\\n   206→     # ... for each agent that had failures\\n   207→     ```\\n   208→   - **Test prompt fix** (e.g., changed wording in a specific test): run that test across all agents that failed it:\\n   209→     ```bash\\n   210→     mise run test:e2e --agent <agent> <TestName>\\n   211→     ```\\n   212→   This step is mandatory — canary tests use the Vogon fake agent and cannot verify agent-specific behavior (trust dialogs, env propagation, config directories, etc.).\\n   213→4. If any step fails, investigate and adjust. Report what happened to the user.\\n   214→\\n   215→For **real-bug** fixes the user approved:\\n   216→1. Apply the fix directly in the working tree (no branch creation)\\n   217→2. Run static checks and unit tests:\\n   218→   ```bash\\n   219→   mise run fmt && mise run lint\\n   220→   mise run test        # Unit tests\\n   221→   mise run test:e2e:canary  # Canary tests\\n   222→   ```\\n   223→3. **Run real E2E tests to verify the fix.** Same scoping rules as flaky fixes above:\\n   224→   - **Agent-specific change** → full suite for that agent\\n   225→   - **Shared CLI/infra change** → full suite for all agents that failed\\n   226→   - **Narrow change** (single test affected) → just that test across affected agents\\n   227→   Skip only if the user explicitly declines (cost concern).\\n   228→4. Report results to the user.\\n   229→\\n   230→### Step 5: Summary\\n   231→\\n   232→Print a summary table:\\n   233→```\\n   234→| Test | Agent(s) | Re-runs | Classification | Action Taken |\\n   235→|------|----------|---------|---------------|-------------|\\n   236→| TestFoo | claude-code | FAIL/PASS/PASS | flaky | Fixed in working tree |\\n   237→| TestBar | all agents | FAIL/FAIL/FAIL | real-bug | Fix applied, tests passing |\\n   238→| TestBaz | opencode | FAIL/PASS/FAIL | flaky | Skipped (user declined) |\\n   239→```\\n   240→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"6f0336a1-6473-4c5b-b17e-4b7595c414f9\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:45:33.791Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a4f91b1ff72fb48e5\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01VEiM5bmK9sCnTqaXtpfURh\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01CHSGpd9mgfnLtAUuoyLCRa\",\"uuid\":\"2dda8b41-8522-470c-8e1f-303908bc7b47\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:45:33.792Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"2dda8b41-8522-470c-8e1f-303908bc7b47\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"00468b34-359e-43a2-b0bb-30677f1aee5e\",\"version\":\"2.1.71\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage-local-only\",\"slug\":\"delegated-hatching-sundae\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:45:35.157Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01WJZVoSGxmzcrCb2RBRnXd7\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01XH8oBfTS7aM1mEcxLEQuz2\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/.claude/skills/e2e-triage/README.md\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":3829,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":67707,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":3829,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":18,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYno7BurbXDZ1BuHkyHm1\",\"uuid\":\"894e9002-00d9-4b25-a272-4d08785b988f\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a4f91b1ff72fb48e5\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01VEiM5bmK9sCnTqaXtpfURh\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01CHSGpd9mgfnLtAUuoyLCRa\",\"uuid\":\"2b77ae17-84ce-4d03-ba6a-0ebecca6b4f3\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:45:35.158Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"2b77ae17-84ce-4d03-ba6a-0ebecca6b4f3\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"00468b34-359e-43a2-b0bb-30677f1aee5e\",\"version\":\"2.1.71\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage-local-only\",\"slug\":\"delegated-hatching-sundae\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01XH8oBfTS7aM1mEcxLEQuz2\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# E2E Triage Skill\\n     2→\\n     3→Triage E2E test failures by re-running tests locally, classifying failures as flaky vs real-bug, and applying fixes interactively.\\n     4→\\n     5→## Usage\\n     6→\\n     7→```\\n     8→# Triage a specific test\\n     9→/e2e-triage TestInteractiveMultiStep\\n    10→\\n    11→# Triage a specific test for one agent\\n    12→/e2e-triage TestInteractiveMultiStep --agent claude-code\\n    13→\\n    14→# Triage multiple tests\\n    15→/e2e-triage TestInteractiveMultiStep TestCheckpointRewind\\n    16→\\n    17→# Analyze existing artifacts (skip re-running)\\n    18→/e2e-triage /path/to/artifact/dir\\n    19→\\n    20→# Download latest CI run artifacts and triage\\n    21→/e2e-triage get latest CI run\\n    22→```\\n    23→\\n    24→The skill will:\\n    25→1. Run the test(s) up to 3 times (first run, re-run on failure, tiebreaker if split)\\n    26→2. Analyze artifacts (`console.log`, `entire.log`, `git-log.txt`, checkpoint metadata)\\n    27→3. Classify each failure and present findings\\n    28→4. Ask before applying any fixes\\n    29→\\n    30→## Classification Logic\\n    31→\\n    32→Re-run results are the primary signal:\\n    33→\\n    34→| Pattern | Classification |\\n    35→|---------|---------------|\\n    36→| FAIL / PASS / PASS | Flaky |\\n    37→| FAIL / PASS / FAIL | Flaky (non-deterministic) |\\n    38→| FAIL / FAIL / PASS | Flaky (non-deterministic) |\\n    39→| FAIL / FAIL / FAIL | Real-bug OR flaky (test-bug) — depends on root cause location |\\n    40→\\n    41→**Key distinction for consistent failures:** if the root cause is in `cmd/entire/cli/` (product code), it's a **real-bug**. If it's in `e2e/` (test infra), it's **flaky (test-bug)**.\\n    42→\\n    43→## Related Skills\\n    44→\\n    45→- `/debug-e2e` — Standalone artifact analysis for diagnosing a specific failure. Use when you already have artifacts and want to understand *what went wrong* without re-running or classifying.\\n    46→- `/e2e-triage` uses debug-e2e's workflow internally for its analysis step, then adds classification (flaky vs real-bug) and automated action.\\n    47→\\n    48→## Key Files\\n    49→\\n    50→- `SKILL.md` — Full skill definition with all steps, classification rules, and action templates\\n    51→- `../../scripts/download-e2e-artifacts.sh` — Downloads artifacts from CI runs\\n    52→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"fea250da-7e81-448c-8a07-1dd6dc64bd76\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:45:35.168Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a4f91b1ff72fb48e5\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01VEiM5bmK9sCnTqaXtpfURh\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01CHSGpd9mgfnLtAUuoyLCRa\",\"uuid\":\"c913f362-eb40-4554-bcfe-191eb5015ae4\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:45:35.176Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"c913f362-eb40-4554-bcfe-191eb5015ae4\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"00468b34-359e-43a2-b0bb-30677f1aee5e\",\"version\":\"2.1.71\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage-local-only\",\"slug\":\"delegated-hatching-sundae\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:45:36.669Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01XSSAmfYy62D5d7dcEmqmED\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01EifDQCyWf17mZ6x8QDzMC6\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/.claude/skills/debug-e2e/SKILL.md\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1123,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":71536,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":1123,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":18,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYno7HoZnGAPDqS26W6zM\",\"uuid\":\"2f6a3e49-ea24-47d8-a78b-8c2354cc143b\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a4f91b1ff72fb48e5\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01VEiM5bmK9sCnTqaXtpfURh\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01CHSGpd9mgfnLtAUuoyLCRa\",\"uuid\":\"58f7c3f4-b378-41c0-b4d7-3494c8091670\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:45:36.670Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"58f7c3f4-b378-41c0-b4d7-3494c8091670\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"00468b34-359e-43a2-b0bb-30677f1aee5e\",\"version\":\"2.1.71\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage-local-only\",\"slug\":\"delegated-hatching-sundae\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01EifDQCyWf17mZ6x8QDzMC6\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→---\\n     2→name: debug-e2e\\n     3→description: Use when investigating E2E test failures from artifacts to diagnose bugs in the Entire CLI, or when pointed at an artifact path for root cause analysis\\n     4→---\\n     5→\\n     6→# Debug Entire CLI via E2E Artifacts\\n     7→\\n     8→Diagnose Entire CLI bugs using captured artifacts from the E2E test suite. Artifacts are written to `e2e/artifacts/` locally or downloaded from CI via GitHub Actions.\\n     9→\\n    10→## Inputs\\n    11→\\n    12→The user provides either:\\n    13→- **A test run directory:** `e2e/artifacts/{timestamp}/` — triage all failures\\n    14→- **A specific test directory:** `e2e/artifacts/{timestamp}/{TestName}-{agent}/` — debug one test\\n    15→\\n    16→## Artifact Layout\\n    17→\\n    18→```\\n    19→e2e/artifacts/{timestamp}/\\n    20→├── report.nocolor.txt          # Pass/fail/skip summary with error lines\\n    21→├── test-events.json            # Raw Go test events (NDJSON)\\n    22→├── entire-version.txt          # CLI version under test\\n    23→└── {TestName}-{agent}/\\n    24→    ├── PASS or FAIL            # Status marker\\n    25→    ├── console.log             # Full operation transcript\\n    26→    ├── git-log.txt             # git log --decorate --graph --all\\n    27→    ├── git-tree.txt            # ls-tree HEAD + checkpoint branch\\n    28→    ├── entire-logs/entire.log  # CLI structured JSON logs\\n    29→    ├── checkpoint-metadata/    # Checkpoint + session metadata\\n    30→    └── repo -> /tmp/...        # Symlink to preserved repo (E2E_KEEP_REPOS=1 only)\\n    31→```\\n    32→\\n    33→## Preserved Repo\\n    34→\\n    35→When the test run was executed with `E2E_KEEP_REPOS=1`, each test's artifact directory contains a `repo` symlink pointing to the preserved temporary git repository. This is the actual repo the test operated on — you can inspect it directly.\\n    36→\\n    37→**Navigate via the symlink** (e.g., `{artifact-dir}/repo/`) rather than resolving the `/tmp/...` path. The symlink lives inside the artifact directory so permissions and paths stay consistent.\\n    38→\\n    39→The preserved repo contains:\\n    40→- Full git history with all branches (main, `entire/checkpoints/v1`)\\n    41→- The `.entire/` directory with CLI state, config, and raw logs\\n    42→- The `.claude/` directory (if Claude Code was the agent)\\n    43→- All files the agent created or modified, in their final state\\n    44→\\n    45→This is the most powerful debugging tool — you can run `git log`, `git diff`, `git show`, inspect `.entire/` internals, and see exactly what the CLI left behind.\\n    46→\\n    47→## Debugging Workflow\\n    48→\\n    49→### 1. Triage (if given a run directory)\\n    50→\\n    51→Read `report.nocolor.txt` to identify failures and their error messages. Each entry shows the test name, agent, duration, and failure output with file:line references.\\n    52→\\n    53→### 2. Read console.log (most important)\\n    54→\\n    55→Full transcript of every operation:\\n    56→- `> claude -p \\\"...\\\" ...` — agent prompts with stdout/stderr\\n    57→- `> git add/commit/...` — git commands\\n    58→- `> send: ...` — interactive session inputs\\n    59→\\n    60→This tells you what happened chronologically.\\n    61→\\n    62→### 3. Read test source code\\n    63→\\n    64→Use the file:line from the report to find the test in `e2e/tests/`. Understand what the test expected to happen vs what console.log shows actually happened.\\n    65→\\n    66→### 4. Diagnose the CLI behavior\\n    67→\\n    68→Cross-reference console.log (what happened) with the test (what should have happened). Focus on CLI-level issues:\\n    69→\\n    70→| Symptom | CLI Investigation |\\n    71→|---------|-------------------|\\n    72→| Checkpoint not created / timeout | Check `entire-logs/entire.log` for hook invocations, phase transitions, errors |\\n    73→| Wrong checkpoint content | Check `git-tree.txt` for checkpoint branch files, `checkpoint-metadata/` for session info |\\n    74→| Hooks didn't fire | Check `entire.log` for missing hook entries (session-start, user-prompt-submit, stop, post-commit) |\\n    75→| Stash/unstash problems | Check `entire.log` for stash-related log lines, `git-log.txt` for commit ordering |\\n    76→| Attribution issues | Check `checkpoint-metadata/` for `files_touched`, session metadata for attribution data |\\n    77→| Strategy mismatch | Check `entire.log` for `strategy` field, verify auto-commit vs manual-commit behavior |\\n    78→\\n    79→### 5. Deep dive files\\n    80→\\n    81→- **entire-logs/entire.log**: Structured JSON logs — hook lifecycle, session phases (`active` → `idle` → `ended`), warnings, errors. Key fields: `component`, `hook`, `strategy`, `session_id`.\\n    82→- **git-log.txt**: Commit graph showing main branch, `entire/checkpoints/v1`, checkpoint initialization.\\n    83→- **git-tree.txt**: Files at HEAD vs checkpoint branch (separated by `--- entire/checkpoints/v1 ---`).\\n    84→- **checkpoint-metadata/**: `metadata.json` has `checkpoint_id`, `strategy`, `files_touched`, `token_usage`, and `sessions` array. Session subdirs have per-session details.\\n    85→\\n    86→### 6. Report findings\\n    87→\\n    88→Identify whether the issue is in:\\n    89→- **CLI hooks** (prepare-commit-msg, commit-msg, post-commit)\\n    90→- **Session management** (phase transitions, session tracking)\\n    91→- **Checkpoint creation** (branch management, metadata writing)\\n    92→- **Attribution** (file tracking, prompt correlation)\\n    93→- **Strategy logic** (auto-commit vs manual-commit behavior)\\n    94→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"18feab47-6c45-4c74-840a-0bb8cb77c690\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:45:36.682Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"a4f91b1ff72fb48e5\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01VEiM5bmK9sCnTqaXtpfURh\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01CHSGpd9mgfnLtAUuoyLCRa\",\"uuid\":\"b0c3eb81-bf98-47e9-a44f-6e945b8cd5e6\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:45:36.684Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"b0c3eb81-bf98-47e9-a44f-6e945b8cd5e6\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"00468b34-359e-43a2-b0bb-30677f1aee5e\",\"version\":\"2.